jobs_des=["Barstool Sports is looking for a talented Jr. Graphic Designer. This position will work closely with mid and senior-level graphic designers to deliver entertaining and visually engaging content. Projects include thumbnail design, logo creation, photoshop compositing/illustrations, graphic templates, social posts, and more. This position will emphasize thumbnail/ social media design and requires a complete understanding of the Adobe Creative Suite. Candidates must understand the Barstool brand and be capable of learning new skills on the fly. Please provide a reel of your motion graphic work and digital and print design portfolio.\n\nWhat You'll Do:\n\nAssist with graphic templates, promos, and social media graphics\nDesign basic animations using digital assets in Adobe After Effects\nCollaborate with team members to design and produce 5-10 professional-quality YouTube thumbnails each week\nDevelop new and imaginative thumbnail concepts based on video footage\nManipulate and retouch images\nCreate & edit graphics for social (YT, X, FB, IG)\nUpdate existing print/digital materials, promos, decks, print/digital ads, and illustrations\nCollaborate with teams across different disciplines (ad sales, marketing, merchandise, communications, etc.)\nMaintain awareness of current industry and technology standards, with a focus on social media and developing trends\n\nWhat You Have:\n\n1+ years of experience in graphic design and motion graphics\nProficiency in Adobe Creative Suite\nExcellent time management and organizational skills\nReady and willing to take on any number of projects as needs arise, adjust priorities, and thrive in a creative and fast-paced environment\nAbility to learn new tools and techniques quickly\nCommitted teammate able to give and receive constructive feedback\nExcellent communication skills (verbal and written)\n\nPay Range: $65,000-$70,000\n\nBarstool Sports is a company that will drive the way media is created and consumed for years to come. Working at Barstool Sports means being part of a team that is solutions-oriented, celebrates creativity, and supports one another.\n\nJoining means having access to competitive and valuable benefits and perks, including but not limited to:\n\nCompetitive medical, dental, and vision insurance; Flexible Spending Accounts and Commuter Benefits\nA 4% 401(k) employer match\nUnlimited vacation time, including Summer break in July and Holiday break in December\nMonthly employer contribution towards cell phone reimbursement\nEmployee discount to the Barstool Sports store\nFinancial wellness benefits through Origin\nA monthly stipend for UberEats\n\nWhat We Value\n\nRep the brand as best you can\nWe have lots of different brains, be open to them\nNever change who you are, that's who we hired\nFind the solution, don't be the problem\nDon't be afraid to try something new\nCommon Sense. Use it.\nBe there for your audience\nAlways think about how you can help\n\nBarstool Sports is for everyone. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender perception or identity, national origin, age, marital status, protected veteran status, or disability status.\n\nBarstool Sports does not accept unsolicited headhunter or agency resumes. Barstool Sports will not pay any third-party agency or company that does not have a signed agreement.", 'Pink Taco Job Description\n\nPosition: GRAPHIC DESIGNER\n\nAs much as we worship the almighty tortilla, we obsess over surrounding ourselves with wonderful energy, culture, and team members. Joining our crew means you’ll play a key role in bringing the spirit of Pink Taco and our menu to life for our fans. We are a company that is focused on growing both our brand and our team members. We want people who love to bring joy to others through great service and delicious tacos. And in return, we strive to create a great work environment.\n\nPURPOSE:\n Responsible for maintaining the brand’s visual look and feel, while helping to advance marketing and operational initiatives. This is who we are: Pink Taco is fun, fair, honest, hardworking, unpretentious, and uncomplicated. We are looking for a passionate graphic designer to be part of our wonderful team.\n DUTIES AND RESPONSABILITES: \nWork directly with Chief Marketing Officer on a wide range of projects and media, including, but not limited to, in-restaurant promotional materials (table tents, signage, menus, posters, banners), brand presentations, advertisements, digital creative for social media, email marketing, and website\nResponsible for working alongside restaurant support center in creating training, HR and operational materials suited for the restaurants and their staff\nCollaboratively ideate with marketing and operations team on new initiatives, maintaining brand consistency and brand voice for all locations across all mediums\nOwn and organize the creative library for the brand\nQUALIFICATIONS AND SKILLS:\n5+ years of experience with design software including Adobe CS, PowerPoint, & other Microsoft Office tools, Canva\nStrong, versatile portfolio of past work completed\nExceptional creativity and innovative design skills, with a strong eye for design, excellent attention to detail\nPassion for being ahead of design trends, and staying relevant to a targeted audience\nExcellent communication and presentation skills\nOrganizational and time management skills for meeting deadlines\nAbility to multitask & pivot in a fast-paced environment\nPrevious experience in hospitality preferred, but not required\n·\nALL WHILE OFFERING:\nCompetitive Pay + Commission\nHealth, Dental and Vision Benefits\nPaid Time Off\nWORKING CONDITIONS:\n The working conditions described below are representative of those a team member encounters while performing the essential duties and responsibilities of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential duties and responsibilities of this job. \n Small to medium office or shared workspace \nFlexibility to Travel\n PHYSICAL REQUIREMENTS:\nWork is performed in an office environment and requires the ability to operate standard office equipment and keyboards. Must have the ability to lift and carry small parcels, packages and other items, to walk short distances, and have the ability to sit and stand for periods of time.\n DISCLAIMER: \nThis job description is a summary of the duties which you as a Graphic Designer are expected to perform in your normal course of work. It is by no means an all-inclusive list but is merely a broad guide to expected duties. You should understand that a job description is neither complete nor permanent; it can be modified at any time with or without notice.', 'Job Title: Junior Graphic Designer\n\nDepartment: Marketing\n\nReports to: Senior Designer\n\nDepartmental Goal: To build Lakers brand affinity and the future fan pipeline by creating daily, engaging team content and leveraging digital platforms, while also helping other departments reach fans and publish their content via digital platforms.\n\nPosition Summary: This position serves as in-house junior graphic designer, developing visual concepts for the Marketing department and any other internal department needing assistance, while maintaining the Lakers brand look and feel.\n\nKey Metrics Used To Evaluate Performance\n\nQuality of graphics created\nAmount and timeliness of projects and jobs completed\nSatisfaction feedback from other internal departments\n\nEssential Functions (Duties & Responsibilities)\n\nCreate assets to be used on Lakers.com, social channels, and email\nProvide event support (e.g. invitations, signage)\nDesign promotional material (e.g. posters, flyers, postcards, etc.)\nServe needs of multiple departments while maintaining visual integrity of the brand\nUp to 50% of time spent on projects for Corporate Partnerships and Ticketing departments\nAssist with event photography (documenting, editing, and posting all aspects of Lakers and South Bay Lakers game days and other off-site events)\nPhotograph select Lakers events (Community Relations, South Bay Lakers, etc.)\nSourcing photography, retouching, and resizing when needed\nAssist with photo shoots, as needed\n\nEducation (Required/ Preferred): Bachelor’s degree in Graphic Design/Fine Arts/Film/Media, or a related field (required)\n\nPrevious Experience\n\nA minimum of one to three (1-3) years working in graphic design\nExperience with photo editing and manipulation of graphics for sponsor mockups and marketing presentations\nPrevious experience in social content creation, advertising, sports, or entertainment is preferred\n\nTechnology Capabilities\n\nAdobe Creative Suite\nAfter Effects, Figma is a plus\nMicrosoft Office (including Excel, Word, Outlook, PowerPoint & Windows)\nCanon photography equipment\n\nKnowledge, Skills, Abilities\n\nHighly organized, motivated and able to prioritize and multi-task under the pressure of deadlines\nStrong understanding of graphic design principles, methods and practices, as well as all phases of design, production, and delivery for web, electronic and print materials\nA fundamental understanding of layout, typography, and photography for print and web\nKnowledge of current design trends and best practices\nKnowledge of production for collateral including resolution, sizes and file types\nAbility to ensure consistent branding standards\nAbility to use production techniques such as color correcting and create clipping paths to prepare files\nAbility to give and take design direction\nExcellent grammatical, spelling, proofreading abilities\nAble to come up with original ideas for designs, as well as integrate ideas from others\nStrong interpersonal skills and the ability to work well with a team\nKnowledge of basketball (preferred)\nExperience in event photography (preferred)\nPrevious experience working with celebrities or professional sports players (preferred)\n\nPhysical Demands: Must be able to lift a min of 25lbs. and walk significant distances in arena on game days\n\nLocation: El Segundo, downtown Los Angeles (Crypto.com Arena for Laker home games), and other occasional off-site events\n\nTravel: Less than 10% of time\n\nHours: Hybrid schedule, 2 days on-site. This position requires constant attention due to the continuous nature of the news cycle. Regular office hours (9am- 5:30pm M-F), must be available to work evenings, weekends and holidays to complete deadlines as needed.\n\nThe pay for this role is $67,000. Actual compensation packages are based on several factors that are unique to each candidate, including but not limited to skill set, depth of experience and certifications\n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, age, disability, gender identity, marital or veteran status, or any other protected class.\n\nBy continuing with an application, you agree to the Lakers Applicant Privacy Policy and Notice.', "Work Mode: Remote\n\nLocation: Remote at Bristol, PA\n\nOpportunity\n\nWe are looking for a graphic designer who can efficiently create engaging and on-brand graphics for both digital/ print projects and short form video while adhering to Robern’s luxury branding requirements.\n\nAssociate will be responsible for the development of communications projects such as [literature brochures, catalogs, eCRM creative, advertising and infographics] while implementing the corporate identity cohesively throughout all touch points. This individual will be self-motivated with strong creative and production skills. Person will be required to take projects from concept through completion with a concentrated effort in elevated typography, design, and layout.\n\nMust have a strong background in design theory, hands-on skills in the latest image and video editing tools such as Adobe Creative Suite, and a promising portfolio.\n\nSpecific Responsibilities\n\nTake projects through the full lifecycle: initiation, research, concept, design/ layout, refinement, and production completion\nProject Management\nEnsure consistency and accuracy of overall brand communications through close attention to detail\nDevelops graphics, illustrations, and other creative materials for the web, social, and other digital platforms that is on-brand, reinforces our status and reputation, and is appropriate for our various audiences- homeowners, trade- Architects & Designers, showrooms\nDesign and animate motion graphics- Gifs, short videos, etc.\nMaintain awareness of current trends in visual arts, advertising, design, printing, and internet applications\nWork closely with Marketing leadership team to ensure a clear understanding of strategic and creative direction of each project\n\n\nSkills/Requirements\n\nBFA/BA in Graphic Design/Commercial Art and 3-7 years Graphic Design experience in an advertising agency, design studio or corporate in-house department\nProficiency in graphic design software, such as Adobe Creative Suite, Photoshop, Illustrator, and InDesign\nCoding ability and familiarity with web design languages, such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript\nCreativity- must have strong concept, design and production ability and affinity to luxury aesthetic\nSolid written and verbal communication skills\nMust be detail oriented and project manage in a fast-paced environment and meet deadlines\nExperience developing strategic visual content for social media\nExperience with developing graphics, illustrations, videos, gifs, and other creative materials for web, social, and other digital platforms\nTechnically proficient with the ability to troubleshoot and problem-solve\nAbility to work independently as well as collaboratively with a diverse group of colleagues\n\n\nApplicants must be authorized to work in the US without requiring sponsorship now or in the future.\n\nThe salary range for this position is $64,600 - $81,350. The specific salary offered to a candidate may be influenced by a variety of factors including the candidate’s experience, their education, and the work location. Available benefits include medical, dental, vision & 401k.\n\nWhy Work at Kohler Co.?\n\nKohler Co.'s mission is to contribute to a higher level of gracious living for those who are touched by our products and services. We understand that it takes investment in our associates’ development to make that happen.So, we offer ongoing investment in each individual’s personal development and the opportunity to collaborate with others across functions and roles at Kohler.\n\nIn addition to the investment in your development, Kohler offers a benefits package including a competitive salary, health, vision, dental, 401(k) with company matching, and more!\n\nImportant update for candidates applying to roles within Kohler Energy, including Power Systems, Engines, Home Energy, Kohler Uninterruptible Power, Clarke Energy, Curtis Instruments, and Heila Technologies. On November 6, Kohler Co. announced the strategic decision to establish Kohler Energy as a separate, independent business with Platinum Equity as the majority investment partner. Kohler will continue to stay invested in the Energy business following the closing and remains committed to supporting the acceleration of long-term growth strategies for both organizations. Talent and operational transition plans are underway, and Kohler Co. and Platinum Equity expect the agreement to close in the first half of 2024.Thank you for your interest in joining our growing team as we embark on the next phase of growth!\n\n\nAbout Us\n\nBeyond the competitive benefits and compensation, Kohler proudly offers a rich history, steeped in creativity and a commitment to our associates and communities.We invite you to learn more about our culture and company at www.kohlercompany.com .\n\nIt is Kohler’s policy to recruit, hire, and promote qualified personnel in all job classifications without regard to race, creed, religion, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, marital status, national origin, disability or status as a protected veteran.If, as an individual with a disability, you need reasonable accommodation during the recruitment process, please contact kohlerjobs@kohler.com . Kohler Co. is an equal opportunity/affirmative action employer.\n\nWe invite you to learn more about equal employment opportunity by reviewing the Federal EEO is the Law and the EEO is the Law Supplement .", "Role: Jr. Graphic Designer\n\nCompany: Born in Los Angeles, Cult Gaia is known for beautiful heirloom pieces that will live in your closet forever. The cornerstone of Cult Gaia's DNA is creating objects d'art that make you look twice. Since its inception, CG has grown from accessories into a lifestyle brand, selling everything from ready-to-wear to shoes, a world of Gaia.\n\nJob Purpose: We are looking for a graphic designer who has a strong sense of layout, typography and composition but also has experience working with images, has an understanding of photography and post-production, and feels very comfortable with retouching, light matching, color grading and color correcting. We are excited to bring on someone who is a true creative, is excited about the fashion industry, and brings an artistic eye with an extreme attention to detail to the team.\n\nReports to: Sr. Graphic Designer\n\nResponsibilities:\nAssist in email design layouts and provide assets for scheduling\nCreate invitations and branded materials as needed\nCreate digital marketing assets for paid media, VIP experiences, text messaging, etc.\nColor correct and retouch garments as needed, both on-model and product images\nAssist in photo selects process\nAssist in reviewing and resizing images\nEnsure on-brand continuity with garments, lighting, and color consistency across the e-commerce, digital platforms, and internal brand collateral\nAssist in file management and organization\nSupport creation of market materials such as look books, invites, etc.\nSupport photoshoot production as needed\nQualifications:\n1-3+ years of experience in graphic design and experience as a photo retoucher and color corrector\nBA/BFA in Graphic Design or other relevant field, or equivalent work experience\nAdobe Creative Suite mastery essential - Photoshop, InDesign, Illustrator\nDirect Marketing background in designing for Email, Social, Web, Display, and Print\nMust have experience in Fashion industry and knowledge of studio photography\nKeen eye for detail and solid grasp of color theory\nStrong typography and composition design skills\nExperience conveying ideas and concepts through storyboarding\nStrong attention to detail and effective communicator\nHighly organized with strong multi-tasking skills\nComfortable working under pressure and meeting tight deadlines\nAbility to have a detail-oriented dialogue about the properties of a given image\nExperience with consumer product and E-commerce photography and retouching is a plus", 'POSITION TITLE: Senior Graphic Designer\n\nLOCATION: NYC office (Hybrid)\n\nJOB TYPE: Full Time\n\nROLE PRIORITIES:\n\nCreate and collaborate with the team to develop on-brand and compelling assets that fulfill the marketing experience objectives\nWork with the team, while utilizing own artistic ability, skills, training, and creativity to help create thoughtful, trend forward design results\n\nKEY RESPONSIBILITIES:\n\nDeveloping and designing marketing materials for seasonal product launches (Emails, Paid Social, Digital, Ecommerce and Social)\nCreate one consistent brand voice across all channels\nPitch concepts for and execute web initiatives, including site updates, emails, banner ads etc.\nExpand on visual identities of the brand, collaborations, and internal initiatives\nCreating Domestic and International Digital asset rollout for e-commerce and affiliate\nSupport in Retail assets for print, digital, and social\nCollaborate with the team to provide design solutions for UX/UI design\nAssist the Senior Art Director with building out decks for internal presentations and pitches and develop new formats, if necessary\nCreate and establish efficient workflows with the team\nOther design projects and responsibilities as assigned\n\nESSENTIAL SKILLS, EXPERIENCE, AND EDUCATION REQUIREMENTS:\n\n5+ years direct design experience preferably within the fashion, beauty, luxury or ad agency space\nBachelor’s degree (Graphic Design, Design, Fine Arts or similar degree)\nAdept multitasker who can shift from task to task\nHighly organized\nRetouching knowledge is preferred\nCommunicative and collaborative team player: comfortable with consistent collaboration across departments and implementing feedback\nAbility to work under tight deadlines\nExcellent attention to detail\nKnowledge of social media platforms\nWell-versed utilization of Photoshop, Illustrator and InDesign\nKnowledge of AfterEffects and Premiere is preferred\n\nBENEFITS:\n\n$75,000 - $90,000 base salary (This range represents the low and high end of the anticipated base salary range for this NYC - based position. The base salary will depend on numerous factors such as: experience and qualifications for the role, experience level, skillset, and balancing internal equity relative to other AO employees.)\n401(k) with an employer match\nMedical, dental, and vision\nGenerous employee discount\n\nThis job description is not an exhaustive list of all functions that the employee may be required to perform, and the employee may be required to perform additional functions. Additionally, the job responsibilities may change at any time as necessitated by business demands.', "This is a hybrid role based out of our HQ in Carlsbad, CA. In-office expectation is 3 days a week*.\n\nWe know from experience that the effects of an active life spent outdoors are profound and can be both the springboard and the foundation for a greater and lasting sense of well-being. And at prAna, we are committed to making products that help get you out there.\n\nWe believe in Nature’s power to better humanity and in humanity’s responsibility to do better by nature. Whether it’s going for a hike at sunrise or taking a walk at sunset, practicing yoga at the beach, or building a campfire after a day of surfing. Looking out from a rock you’ve just climbed or looking down from the wall you’ve just mastered. We believe the most important step you take on your journey to well-being is the one that takes you beyond your doorstep.\n\nAbout The Position\n\nThe Graphic Designer is a key member of the creative team who works closely with the Web Designers, Graphic Designers, Marketing, and Art Directors to create and support social, digital, and web-based creative for prAna. The Graphic Designer is responsible for creating graphics for prAna’s social media, site, and marketing efforts. The Graphic Designer will carry out projects as directed by Creative Leadership, with high attention to detail and accuracy, in an aesthetic that aligns with the prAna brand.\n\nHow You’ll Make a Difference\n\nCreate visual assets, graphics, and layouts needed for marketing efforts (various digital assets with a focus on social media)\nWork directly with the Art Director to bring marketing and brand campaigns to life\nMultitask and execute multiple small & mid-sized projects\nUnderstand and troubleshoot brand elements as they relate to visual design\nAccurately follow briefs and execute design projects, paying close attention to details\nFollow brand guidelines and creative direction to produce visual assets (static and video) with a focus on social media\nProactively seek necessary information on project requirements to ensure clarity and alignment on timelines, deliverables, stakeholders, and hand-offs\nWork collaboratively & iteratively with Art Directors, marketing, and channel leads, to execute the vision of the brief.\nMaintain best practices for social media, web, and digital design\n\nYOU ARE\n\nCreative and can execute strong ideas and elevate the design aesthetic of prAna\nA climbing, and/or yoga enthusiast\nAble to work autonomously and cross-functionally with ease\nAn agile team player who’s comfortable both following a plan and adapting when it changes\n\nYOU HAVE\n\nBachelor’s Degree in Design, or an equal combination of experience and education\n3-5 years working experience as a Graphic Designer\nMust be highly proficient with current versions of Adobe Creative Suite\nProven understanding of the principals of design, color theory, composition, typography, photography, and the ability to implement them to create dynamic on-brand creative and solutions\nStay on top of design trends for various brand and marketing channels and continually foster optimization and evolution of style\nA passion for brand building and social media\nPORTFOLIO LINK REQUIRED EITHER ON RESUME OR APPLICATION\n\nSalary Range: $59,300 - $91,900\n\n#prAna\n\n#hybrid\n\nWe create versatile, stylish, and sustainable clothing and accessories that you can wear during every activity, every adventure, every day. How do we know? Because we base our designs on our own experiences. You see we’re more than makers, we’re doers—yogis, climbers, and world travelers—and we use our knowledge to make adventurous, free-spirited clothes that look good and play hard.\n\nThis job description is not meant to be an all-inclusive list of duties and responsibilities, but constitutes a general definition of the position's scope and function in the company.\n\nColumbia Sportswear is an equal opportunity employer. We evaluate qualified applicants without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, veteran status, and other legally protected characteristics. The Know Your Rights poster is available here: https://www.eeoc.gov/poster The pay transparency policy is available here: https://www.dol.gov/sites/dolgov/files/OFCCP/pdf/pay-transp_%20English_formattedESQA508c.pdf Columbia Sportswear is committed to working with and providing reasonable accommodations to individuals with disabilities. If you need a reasonable accommodation because of a disability for any part of the employment process, please notify your recruiter.", "POSITION: Graphic Designer, Luxury Optical Holdings (Retail)\n We are looking for a profressional Graphic Designer to join the Marketing/Brand team that drives our Retail brands & businesses. This role is integral in creating beautiful, effective assets that define our luxury eyewear experiences across all channels & touchpoints including in-store, online, at tradeshows / events and at our corporate office.\n RESPONSIBILITIES:\n ·     Concept, create and deliver effective creative marketing ideas & designs including seasonal campaigns, digital/print assets for retail and wholesale, retail signage, packaging, advertising, email campaigns, websites, retail windows, trade shows, social media, press and sales collateral—leading the design process from ideation to creative development to execution.\no  Ideation includes:\n§ Concept presentations with idea write ups and any reference images or examples need to communicate the idea to internal stakeholders. Must support business objectives and relevant contextual realities like consumer insights, retail insights, market insights, competitive insights, media and best practices.\no  Creative development includes:\n§ Understanding of branding strategy\n§ Elevated & impeccable design standards\n§ Strong understanding of how to hero product in various contexts (product shots, in-situation, on-model) from an art direction, design and photography standpoint.\n§ Excellent typographic skills.\n§ Strong attention to detail around each aspect of the customer experience.\no  Execution includes:\n§ Well versed in production processes and technical specifications.\n§ Manage release of assets and proof review process\n§ Provide final approval to ensure the highest integrity for the final work\n§ Manage communications around deliveries and internal expectation management\n·     Fluent in design, fashion, tech and retail trends, as well as visual history.\n·     Work closely with internal teams to translate projects and needs into actionable creative solutions.\n·     Develop a strong understanding of the Morgenthal Frederics and ROBERT MARC NYC brands, products, and audiences in order to maximize visual communication.\n·     Work with agencies, outside contractors, photographers, videographers, etc. on creative projects\n·     Opportunity to shoot original content for owned social channels.\n·     Evolve brand guidelines, develop digital guidelines and creative templates, and uphold established creative standards and brand consistency across all projects and corporate departments.\n SKILLS:\n·     Understands visual/design best practices and industry standards/trends\n·     Experience driving results within omni-channel Retail space\n·     Extremely detail oriented, organized and capable of managing creative assets, photos, etc.\n·     Motivated self-starter with a no-task-too-big-or-too-small attitude, comfortable with handling multiple priorities at once.\n·     Solutions-oriented thinker flexible to time constraints and the needs of a fast-paced, small office environment.\n·     Able to communicate effectively on project management needs and timelines.\n·     Able to present the work, ideas and design decisions.\n·     A champion of great design.\n REQUIREMENTS:\n·     3-5 years of experience\n·     Highly proficient in Adobe Suite (InDesign, Photoshop and Illustrator).\n·     Working knowledge of video editing and animation software like AfterEffects.\n·     Proficient in photography.\n·     Portfolio of work featuring both print and digital, showing mastery of visual communication and an elevated, luxury aesthetic.\n·     Knowledge of web design program a plus\n·     Illustration experience a plus\n  ABOUT LUXURY OPTICAL HOLDINGS\nLuxury Optical Holdings (LOH) is a leading independent retailer of luxury and premium eyewear with specialty eyewear stores across the United States. Currently 35 stores are comprised of independent retail concepts as well as two owned eyewear brands that set the standard for design and craftsmanship, and pioneer specialty luxury materials including sustainable buffalo horn. All stores sell premium and luxury 3rd party eyewear brands with strong brand recognition worldwide.\n Our two product & retail brands include:\nROBERT MARC NYC designs and discovers New York’s most wanted eyewear. Inspired by the city it’s called home since 1981, RMNYC has always harnessed the vitality of New York City and proudly outfits some of its most renowned personalities. Known for its trademark hinge, RMNYC frames represent the marriage of style and fit. \n MORGENTHAL FREDERICS has been creating, curating and caring for the world's finest eyewear since 1913. Each heirloom-quality piece is exemplary in its curation and composition, using sustainably sourced buffalo horn milled by master artisans in Germany, handcrafted acetate from Germany & Japan, and the finest Japanese titanium.\n Our retail brands include:\n·     Eye Q Intelligent Eyewear (Rochester, MN)\n·     Georgetown Opticians (Washington, DC)\n·     Leonard Opticians (NYC)\n·     Optica (Troy, MI)\n·     Opticians 3 (Chestnut Hill, MA)\n·     Riehle Optician (Warwick, NY)\n·     Specs Optical (Minneapolis, MN)\n·     Salle Opticians (Atlanta, GA)", 'Job Description\n\nAbout the Graphic Design Role\n\nWe are looking for a versatile and proactive graphic designer to join our cross-brand design team as the primary creative dedicated to our growing loyalty program, The Key Rewards. This is a unique role within the company— supporting all WSI brands on a wide variety of projects, from digital, web, in-store signage, print, UI and more. This role will work closely with the cross-brand creative manager and creative director across all campaign phases—from initial concepting through to launch. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in graphic design and/or production design, an eye for detail, and a solid understanding of design systems. We value those with enthusiastic attention-to-detail, consistent and reliable delivery, a readiness to jump into new challenges, are quick to learn and adapt, and will proactively communicate and problem-solve.\n\nEssential Functions\n\n\nCollaborate with the digital creative team to execute polished designs from concept to launch. You are confident translating direction from the earliest ideation phases all the way through final delivery across multiple mediums\nDevelop and maintain a consistent visual identity and brand presence across all loyalty projects\nCreate digital assets including banners, landing pages, email templates, social media graphics, and other promotional materials\nProduce designs that effectively communicate complex concepts and information in an aesthetically pleasing and user-friendly manner\nCollaborate with cross-functional teams, including marketing, site, and development, to ensure designs align with project goals and objectives\nStay up-to-date with the latest design trends, techniques, and industry best practices to continuously improve the quality and effectiveness of designs\nAssist in managing and organizing design assets, ensuring they are easily accessible and maintained for future use\nParticipate in design reviews and provide constructive feedback to maintain and elevate design standards\nEnsure designs are delivered on time and meet established deadlines\nAdapt to changing priorities and handle multiple projects simultaneously, balancing quality and efficiency\n\n\nCriteria\n\n\nBachelor’s degree in Visual, Web, Graphic Design or equivalent experience\nProven experience as a graphic designer with a focus on digital design, preferably in the retail/loyalty industry or related field. Multi-brand retail is a plus\nProficiency in design software such as Figma, and Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, etc.)\nA strong critical-thinker that is solutions-focused. Able to foresee and assess possible issues and quickly problem-solve—does not let complications slow them down\nStrong portfolio showcasing a range of design work, demonstrating attention to detail, and a solid understanding of design principles\nExcellent understanding of best practices and usability principles\nAbility to work collaboratively in a cross-functional team environment and effectively communicate design concepts and rationale\nExperience in creating and maintaining branding guidelines and design systems\nStrong organizational and time-management skills, with the ability to prioritize tasks and meet deadlines effectively\nAny additional experience with light video/animation, UI/UX design, or copywriting is a big plus\nAbility to perform work onsite in the San Francisco corporate office\n\n\nBenefits\n\nOnce you are here, you can look forward to a wide variety of benefits designed to help you grow, personally and professionally, to keep you healthy, to prepare you for the unexpected, to care for your family and to build a secure future. Depending on your position and your location, here is a look at what you might be eligible for:\n\n\nA generous discount on all Williams Sonoma Inc. brands through multiple shopping channels\nA 401(k) plan and other investment opportunities\nPaid vacations, holidays and other time-off programs\nHealth benefits, including health, dental and vision insurance; health and dependent care tax-free spending accounts; medical, family and bereavement leave; same-sex domestic partner benefits; short- and long-term disability programs; life and travel insurance; an employee assistance program\nTax-free commuter benefits\nA wellness program that supports your physical, financial and emotional health\nIn-person and online learning opportunities through WSI University\nCross-brand and cross-function career opportunities\nLocation specific sample sales\nA business casual work environment\nSan Francisco based bike share program\nTime off to volunteer\nMatching donations to qualifying nonprofit organizations\nCompany-sponsored community involvement\nVarious discounts on local businesses\n\n\nThe expected starting pay range for this position is $70,000 -$80,000. Applicable pay ranges may differ across markets. Actual pay will be determined based on experience and other job-related factors permitted by law. In addition to competitive pay, compensation may include a variety of other components like benefits, paid time off, merit, and bonus opportunities.\n\nWilliams-Sonoma, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer.\n\nWilliams-Sonoma, Inc. will consider for employment qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the requirements of the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance, or other applicable state or local laws and ordinances.\n\nWSI will not now or in the future commence an immigration case or "sponsor" an individual for this position (for example, H-1B or other employment-based immigration.)\n\nThis role is not eligible for relocation assistance.\n\nAbout Us\n\nOur Company\n\nFounded in 1956, Williams-Sonoma, Inc. is the premier specialty retailer of high-quality products for the kitchen and home in the United States. Our family of brands are Williams Sonoma, Williams Sonoma Home, Pottery Barn, Pottery Barn teen, pottery barn kids, Rejuvenation, Mark & Graham, west elm, or Outward. These brands are among the best known and most respected in the industry. We offer beautifully-designed, stylish and functional products for every area of the home, including the kitchen, living room, bedroom, home office, closet, laundry room and even outdoor spaces. We\'ve seen some big changes since our first brick-and-mortar store opened more than half of a century ago. What hasn\'t changed is our passion for high-quality products, functional design, outstanding customer service, and enhancing the lives of our customers and the communities where we operate. Today, we\'re a multi-brand, multi-channel, global enterprise supported by state-of-the-art technology and some of the most talented teams in retailing - and we\'re always looking for new energy and ideas.', "It's fun to work in a company where people truly BELIEVE in what they're doing!\n\nWe're committed to bringing passion and customer focus to the business.\n\nThe Junior Graphic Designer will work with a team of digital designers to conceptualize and create compelling designs for Peter Millar’s online properties. This role will work in a collaborative team environment and advance the brand’s e-commerce business, social handles and digital assets. From a skillset standpoint, this role has digital design experience, with basic front-end HTML/CSS talents. The position requires the ability to concept, produce, proof, test, and troubleshoot effective digital assets that adhere to our brand standards. This role should have an interest in general user interface & user experience design.\n\nEssential Functions\n\nAssist and own monthly content and work with the Managers of Digital Design to ensure assets are to brand standards. The Junior Graphic Designer will also present their designs in review meetings with the digital design team and PDFing their work for review.\nResearch creative trends in competitive markets and apply that knowledge and learning to development of new marketing and digital projects\nArticulate ideas and push to bring new ideas to the Peter Millar website, marketing, social and digital assets while adhering to brand standards.\nWork closely with the Director of Digital Design on new campaign ideas for both digital and social assets.\nContinually improve the web to support marketing objectives and give customers an outstanding customer experience.\nConceive and create design solutions that address both the user’s goals as well as business goals.\nConcept and produce design work for primarily web projects that include, but are not limited to: email campaigns, website/homepage creative updates, web banners, social media and more.\nDevelop & assist in identifying strategic web creative to drive site conversion & improved customer (user) experience.\nExecute web projects from design concepts using Peter Millar’s web Platform, images and light HTML/CSS.\n\nCompetencies\n\nUnderstand foundational design concepts (i.e. spatial relations & typography), and also be an out of the box thinker to create new experiences within our design aesthetic.\nCan work effectively in a fast-paced environment with rapidly shifting priorities.\nUnderstand web technologies as they effect presentation layer options and functionality.\nAbility to collaborate successfully with other creative designers, copywriters and business owners.\nExpert knowledge and skills in Adobe XD, Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign and Figma.\n\nDesired Education And Experience\n\nDegree in Design or equivalent experience in a web design role.\n2+ years of experience\n\nIf you like wild growth and working with happy, enthusiastic over-achievers, you'll enjoy your career with us!", "🎥 Video about this role from Amped.io's founder Matt on why this role:\nhttps://tella.video/ampedio-design-role-2024-gr4m\n\nIf you believe in loving your neighbor as yourself, being a good steward, and working together as a family in the pursuit of passion (P.S. our company values), a role at Amped might be for you.\nYou’ll be designing web based experiences for some of the top brands in Ecommerce. Specifically we build pop ups and elements that go on top of the existing site. You’ll be designing and split testing with companies directly impacting millions of dollars in revenue for these ecommerce companies. We’re looking for someone to join us in our Raleigh, NC office.\n\n🚀ABOUT AMPED.IO\nAt Amped.io, we make it easy for DTC ecom brands to maximize customer acquisition and grow faster than ever through beautiful popups. Capture more email and sms subscribers, collect preferences + zero-party data, and drive real revenue results.\nAt Amped you'll have the opportunity to become a key player in driving our future success. We’re a small team of 15 people with a strong culture that is uniquely built on our values of loving your neighbor as you do yourself, being a good steward of our clients and ourselves, working together as a family, and the pursuit of passion.\n\n🙋\u200d♂️ WHAT YOU’LL DO\nYou will work directly with Client Success Managers to lead the  creative direction of our client’s campaigns. You will be involved from the origination of new campaign ideas, to strategy, creating the prototypes, and setting them up in our software and occasionally working with our developers to make them a reality.\nUsing the client's brand voice and style, you will create visually striking graphics that persuade, guide, and encourage action through user interface and experience design.\nYou will help write persuasive copy that will compel visitor interaction and ultimately conversion.\nManage design projects, both on an individual and a team level.\nYou’ll be responsible for maintaining a high level of design excellence across our client accounts in a proactive manner.\nCreate designs in the Amped.io editor and setup Campaigns while also constantly looking for ways to improve the UI/UX of our own software\nManage overall experience of Amped technology on the client’s site, taking into consideration the user journey on the client’s site through conversion funnel.\n\n📜 REQUIREMENTS\nFirst and foremost, we want a passionate person who is ready and willing to go the extra mile for their team and client.\nWeb design experience is key - You will not be writing code but you must have experience designing for the web\nExpert in Figma and Photoshop\nKnowledgeable in UI/UX practices and trends\nStrong attention to detail (a must for us)\nAble to think analytically to solve usability challenges with simple to understand, yet expertly styled graphics\nPossess a keen eye for intuitive design, color, and layout with a strong knowledge of typography\nExperience in CSS & HTML a plus but not required\nAble to follow style guides and design templates of client brands, as well as in-house best practices\nStrong written and communication skills, able to organize designs to effectively communicate ideas.\nAble to thrive in a fast-paced, collaborative, high pressure environment whilst tracking multiple ongoing projects\nGood stewardship of responsibilities given, with the flexibility to take on those that aren’t!\nA student of life: self-motivated to learn everyday, always pushing to understand more about the goals and outcomes of a project, and in failure the ability to see insight, and take that to drive the next project.\nHumility; able to take and give opinions, and understand that we’re a small team, but we’re all you’ve got.\n\n💶 FULL BENEFITS\nSalary: Compensation based on experience\nEmployee Health Benefits: Healthcare coverage with dental and vision plans\n401(k): We offer up to a 4% match\nPaid Time Off: We offer PTO, paid holidays, bereavement, and remote work\n\n📬 TO APPLY\nPlease email apply@amped.io with the subject line of “Applying for the Design Role”, with your resume, a link to your portfolio & Linkedin Profile, and a quick intro as to why you would be a good candidate for this role.", "Location: Oklahoma City, Oklahoma\n\nJob Type: Permanent\n\nCompensation Range: $44,000 - 50,000 per year\n\nOur client in the Arts & Crafts sector is seeking a passionate Graphic Designer to join their vibrant team in Oklahoma City. The company prides itself on fostering creativity, innovation, and excellence in the creation of exclusive art collections and design solutions.\n\nAs a Graphic Designer, you will play a pivotal role in conceptualizing and developing creative design solutions. You will work independently and collaboratively within a dynamic team environment to create exceptional artwork, maintaining consistency with brand standards and objectives.\n\nThis is a direct-hire role, offering an exciting opportunity to collaborate with talented professionals and contribute to a creative journey.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nCollaborate effectively with leadership, clients, and cross-functional teams to develop innovative design solutions.\nContribute to the development of seasonal and everyday art collections, enriching our archive of exclusive art.\nProduce inspirational artwork, sketches, mood boards, graphics, layouts, and visuals to support project objectives.\nReview final designs to ensure alignment with departmental and corporate brand standards.\nStay updated with art, typography, design, and marketing trends for ongoing inspiration.\nMaintain accurate project records and monitor progress through MARVIN and other team records.\nProactively anticipate and troubleshoot potential obstacles to maintain project momentum.\nDeliver high-quality work consistently, even under tight deadlines.\nFoster positive working relationships across departments to ensure a cohesive creative process.\nMaintain a clean and organized work station while being adaptable to additional tasks as needed.\n\n\nQualifications:\n\nExperience level: Experienced\nMinimum 2 years of experience\nEducation: Bachelors\nPrevious experience or qualifications in a related field with demonstrable professional graphic design skills.\nStrong sense of color, style, typography, and design.\nProficient in Mac and Microsoft Office applications.\nKnowledgeable about relevant software, techniques, and industry trends.\nExcellent analytical, research, and presentation skills.\nOpenness to feedback and a collaborative mindset.\nStrong work ethic, flexibility, reliability, and accountability.\nAbility to problem-solve with patience and intelligence.\nSelf-motivated with excellent time management and multitasking abilities.\nOutstanding communication, negotiation, and collaboration skills.\nWillingness and ability to perform duties at the corporate office in Oklahoma City.\n\n\nJOBID: 1017363\n\nEqual Opportunity Employer: Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Sexual Orientation, Gender Identity, National Origin, Age, Genetic Information, Disability, Protected Veteran Status, or any other legally protected group status.\n\nAt Cella, a randstad digital company, we welcome people of all abilities and want to ensure that our hiring and interview process meets the needs of all applicants. If you require a reasonable accommodation to make your application or interview experience a great one, please contact HRsupport@randstadusa.com.\n\nPay offered to a successful candidate will be based on several factors including the candidate's education, work experience, work location, specific job duties, certifications, etc. In addition, Cella by randstad digital offers a comprehensive benefits package, including health, an incentive and recognition program, and 401K contribution (all benefits are based on eligibility).", "Company Description\n\nAt rue21, we believe fashion should be fun and accessible to all. As a leading specialty retailer, we’re different, we’re unique—just like you. rue21 combines a shopping experience designed to fit the individuality of our customers with a community to foster love, advocate change and empower each other through what we wear and what we do. Join our team and be #YOUinrue.\n\nJob Description\n\nThe Graphic Designer contributes to rue21’s results by working closely with Creative team concepting and designing in-store and digital campaigns and advertising materials that creatively and consistently reflect the company's fashion-forward brand identity. A substantial degree of creativity is expected. Flexibility, adaptability and the ability to learn quickly in various technical and creative environments, while delivering quality work within tight deadlines, are key attributes of this position.\n\nCommits to supporting rue21’s vision, mission, and values of an inclusive environment and sets an example for their team or sphere of influence.\nResponsible for designing and developing all projects from concept to production, to include: creating original designs and developing art for point-of-purchase, presentations, advertisements, web, and creating graphics for Company presentations\nManaging multiple design projects which involves collaborating and supporting cross-functional internal business partners in creating necessary artwork related to rue21 branding initiatives\nWorking closely with the Creative team on the design and production of all in-store campaigns and web assets\n\nQualifications\n\nBachelor’s Degree in Graphic Design or related field\n2-3 years of experience\nExpertise in InDesign, Photoshop, and Illustrator. After Effects would be preferred\nStrong, conceptual thinker who possesses a wide range of design capabilities including web design, emails, branding, typography, catalog production, and retail graphics\nPrior retail experience preferred\nHigh degree of proficiency in MS Office Suite, Outlook & Internet applications\nStrong analytical, prioritizing, interpersonal, problem-solving, and presentation skills\nAbility to operate independently while establishing strong working relationships with co-workers and cross-functional teams\nStrong, professional and effective verbal and written communication skills\nAbility to foster a positive and motivating work environment, encouraging feedback and innovation\nSelf-motivated with critical attention to detail, deadlines and reporting\nAbility to adapt well to change in direction and priority in a fast- paced and deadline-oriented environment\n\nAdditional Information\n\nAdditional Information\n\nCompetitive compensation and bonus plan\n\nComprehensive Benefit Package\n\nGenerous PTO offerings\n401K Retirement Plan with company match\nMedical, Dental and Vision Coverage\nCompany sponsored Life Insurance\nHealth Savings Account\nFlexible Spending Account/Dependent Care\nEmployee Assistance Program - Confidential support programs for associates and families\n\nEmployee Discounts\n\n40% off full price merchandise in stores and on-line\nPerks at Work – Savings program on brands, travel, dining, and more\n\nThis summary of benefits is reflective of a range of those available and may not apply to all employees.", 'Company Description\n\nHeadquartered in Southern California, Skechers has spent 30 years helping men, women and kids everywhere look and feel good. Developing comfort technologies is at the foundation of all that we do—delivering stylish, innovative, and quality products at a reasonable price. From our diverse footwear offering to a growing range of apparel and accessories, Skechers is a complete lifestyle brand.\n\nWith international business representing over half of our total sales, we have product available in more than 180 countries and significant opportunities for continued expansion worldwide. We sell our collections direct to consumers through more than 4,450 Skechers stores around the globe and Skechers e-commerce sites, as well as through a network of third-party partners.\n\nA MULTI-BILLION-DOLLAR GLOBAL LEADER IN THE FOOTWEAR INDUSTRY.\n\nJob Description\n\nJOB PURPOSE-\n\nAs an Assistant Graphic Designer / Print Specialist, you will play a pivotal role in supporting the creation of visually compelling printed marketing materials with a specific focus on apparel presentation. Working closely with Senior Graphic Designers and the Design Director, you will contribute to the development of brand books, hang tags, catalogs, and other print assets. Your expertise in typography, photography, layout, and color theory will be crucial to assisting in the creation of cohesive graphic stories for each apparel delivery and category.\n\nEssential Job Results-\n\nExpert Adobe InDesign Proficiency:\nUtilize Adobe InDesign for expert catalog layout and design.\nDemonstrate proficiency in typography using Adobe Fonts.\nCreative Design Contributions:\nEdit digital photography with precision and correction techniques.\nCapture and edit digital videos related to apparel presentation.\nConceptualize, draw, and illustrate graphics, maintaining a refined eye for detail.\nCollaborate on placement art, including graphics, embroideries, and embellishments.\nPrepare artwork for production, ensuring accurate scaling, color callouts, and vendor communication.\nEdit purchased art, adjusting patterns, colorways, and indexing in Photoshop.\nUse Photoshop and Illustrator to create and set up artwork.\nEffective Collaboration and Communication:\nManage stakeholder requests, establish priorities and deadlines, and respond promptly.\nOrganize and maintain libraries of creative assets.\nCollaborate closely with Apparel Designers, Marketing, and Packaging teams.\nAdditional Responsibilities-\n\nStay updated on graphic trends through research and market shopping.\n\nSupervisory Responsibilities-\n\nNone\n\nQualifications\n\nREQUIREMENTS-\n\n3-5 years of applied experience working as a Graphic Designer within an apparel or print company preferred.\nKnowledge of print production a plus.\nKnowledge of Digital Photography and how to import/manipulate digital media.\nDesign skills including drawing/sketching, painting, typography, color theory, texture and visual presentation.\nIllustrates a dedication to meeting requirements of internal and external customers, responding to all customer requests promptly and thoroughly.\nStrong communication skills including the ability to work in a team environment, give honest, direct feedback and is a solid verbal and written communicator.\nMeets deadlines, prioritizes appropriately, copes well with change, and maintains composure under pressure.\nIs accountable for results, approaches obstacles proactively and looks for ways to resolve problems and issues.\nAdvanced Adobe Programs (Photoshop, Illustrator, and InDesign etc.) skills required.\nKnowledge of Microsoft Office Suite and other basic computer programs.\nExperience with MAC.\nBasic knowledge of Flex PLM. Loading graphic matrix to web-based database.\n\nEducation And Experience-\n\nFormal Training (certified) and/or educational background in Graphic Arts required. AA or BA in Graphic Arts / Fine Arts / Illustration preferred.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nTo perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. The skills, abilities and physical demands described are representative of those duties that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodation may be made to enable individuals with disabilities, who are otherwise qualified for the job position, to perform the essential functions.\n\nPHYSICAL DEMANDS-\n\nThe physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.\n\nWhile performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to stand; use hands to finger, handle, or feel, and talk or hear. The employee frequently is required to walk; sit, reach with hands and arms, and stoop, kneel. The employee is occasionally required to sit for long period of times.\n\nAll your information will be kept confidential according to EEO guidelines.\n\nPay range for this position is $33-$36/hr\n\nBenefits\n\nPaid Parental Leave: including time for fathers and adopting parents.\nShort term & long term disability and life insurance at no cost to the employee.\nExtensive medical, dental, and vision plans with multiple carries, including EPO, HPN and PPO plans.\nCompetitive 401k plan and employer matching.\nHealth Savings Account (HSA) and Flexible Savings Account (FSA) offerings.\nPaid vacation, sick, personal and holiday time.\nPet Insurance available.\nOnsite wellness programs at company headquarters including fitness classes, acupuncture, and chiropractor.\nEmployee stock purchase program\nEmployee product discount of 50%; employee sample sales and family and friends discount throughout the year.\nSkechers Company Culture and growth strategy is deeply infused with internal career growth and opportunities for learning.', "Corporate Graphic Designer\n$90,000 - $110,000 + 10% Bonus (BASED ON PREFORMANCE)\n3-5 Years of Experiance\nHybrid 2 days in office\nOur client in New York City, NY\n\nKey Qualifications: Designing for digital, print, data visualization, and infographic.\n\nB2B- Internal and External Communications and designs\n\nJob Summary:\nUnder general direction, the Graphic Designer role supports the Corporate Communications function by creating compelling, on-brand visual content for multiple communications platforms and channels in collaboration with a variety of internal and external stakeholders.\n\nDuties/Responsibilities:\nTranslate brand stories and data into clear, compelling visual presentations\nDevelop branded charts, graphs, tables, icons, illustrations and infographics\nProduce consistent and compelling graphics across digital formats as well as print when needed\nWork with a broad range of internal stakeholders to complete projects on time and on brand\nEnsure design compliance with project needs and visual brand standards\nDevelop and execute designs and visual branding for internal communication products and services including online, print, multimedia, presentation, display and other interactive collateral\nConduct research, conceptualize and develop several strong, persuasive ideas that address the goals and purpose of our clients company\nAbility to be a self-starter, pay strict attention to detail, and multitask across multiple projects in a fast-paced environment\nPartner with stakeholders to understand goals, strategies and target audiences\nAttend and participate in collaborative brainstorming sessions\nServe as creative resource and point of contact for management on design and branding standards, vendor selection and production methods and timelines\nResearch emerging technologies and recommend solutions that align with business goals\nMay provide photographic support for internal events/activities\nPerforms other duties as assigned\n\nJob Specific Knowledge\nRequired\nAbility to work with the client to define project requirements and provide process advice for optimal visual communication production\nA strong portfolio\nProven understanding of layout, color, typography and imagery\nExcellent written, verbal and visual communication skills\nExceptional time management skills and attention to detail\nPreferred\nKnowledge of human-centered design methodology or design thinking principles\nKnowledge of WordPress, Joomla!, Content Management Systems, or HTML and CSS\nEducation, Certification and Experience:\nRequired\nBachelor's degree in Fine Art, Graphic Design or related field\nMinimum three years of graphic design experience in a corporate or agency setting\nProficient with Adobe Creative Cloud (i.e., Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign)\nProficient with Keynote and Microsoft Office\nExperience in facilitating discussions with clients about complex workforce messages, data representations, and analytic ideas\nPreferred\nExperience with data visualization and infographic production\nExperience with adhering to brand management guidelines", "The Graphic Designer creates all website/social/email/advertising graphic designs and brand creative needs. This role is responsible for developing designs in line with the brand design guidelines. The workload includes translating seasonal visual brand direction into seasonal designs, and execution across channels and platforms. This role is also responsible for sourcing and overseeing all print production. This role reports to the Art Director.\n\nCollaborate with Marketing and Creative core team to execute the tone set by the brand's Art Director to bring our brand’s seasonal vision to life\nCreate all brand collateral and assets for web, email, social, advertising, etc. (see example projects below\nParticipate in weekly creative briefing and status meetings with Project Manager and work with PM to develop, coordinate and meet all project timelines.\nSource and oversee any print production\n\nProjects may include but are not limited to:\n\nRetouching and optimizing brand photos\nAbility to create digital assets (including photo, video/motion, animations, etc.)\nCreation of social assets (GIF’s, REELS, Stories, Animation)\nDesign of invites\nGifting outreach collateral\nPackaging design\nEvent Collateral\nEmails\n\n\nSocial promo\nPhysical (menus, signs)\nBusiness cards\nMerchandising Projects:\nCreate seasonal line sheet of clothing line by collaborating with design and merchandising team\n\n\nPhysical collateral for brand + promo\nMural\nBusiness cards\nHand outs\nDigital ads (subway, arena boards, etc.)\nPrint ads\nDigital collateral for brand channels\nSocial\nPaid\nweb\nSeasonal Look books for Merchandising\nResizing/Cropping images for PDP as needed\nAdding special banners to PDP images\nMonthly Brand/Product/Campaign Instagram stories & posts\nMonthly Paid Media\nMonthly homepage updates\nWorking closely with digital to design out collection/special pages\nMonthly Sale creative (Paid, Web, Social)\nCommunicating with Marketing & Creative to align and balance strategy, messaging, and visual creative\nWorking with Marketing to determine overall strategy for a given execution (campaign, gift guide, sale, seasonal, product focus)\nCommunicating and working closely with Digital + Social teams to create content that is tailored to perform on each platform while working closely with Art Director to make sure all content is visually aligned with brand and up to standards\nOrganizing and delivering assets through Dropbox\nPartner/Collab promotional asset creation\nPassing brand + photo assets to partners\nCropping campaign images for social + paid (1x1, 4x5, 9x16) (with + without logo)\nVideo editing/finessing as needed (swapping out sounds, cropping videos, repurposing old videos)\nMotion/Animation as needed (flat gifs for paid, animated text + graphics for social)\nGoogle banner ads\nSocial banner updates (YouTube, Pinterest, Linked in, Facebook)\nHelping with creative decks as needed\n\nSkills Needed:\n\nMUST have previous experience in an advertising agency or similar high-paced, heavy workload environment\nMust be a digital native and have previous experience working on retail/fashion or beauty brands\nMust possess a thorough understanding of interactive communications and delivery systems, processes, and user interface design as well as retail industry best practices\nHave a strong knowledge of layouts, graphic fundamentals, typography & limitations of the web\nPossess print and web design capabilities: must know how to work in both media for integrated campaigns\nAbility to lead projects from concept to completion. Apply best practices in user interface and interactive design, including image optimization and site mapping\nExperience with software such as Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign & Flash\nExperience with Adobe After Effects & video editing (a plus)\nAbility to manage multiple projects from concept through completion\n\nSalary: $85,000 - $90,000", "Who We Are\n\nAuthentic is a global brand development, marketing and entertainment platform. Authentic elevates and builds the long-term value of more than 50 consumer brands and properties by partnering with best-in-class manufacturers, wholesalers and retailers. We are a Lifestyle and Entertainment platform comprising value-driving business models and global brands. Authentic creates sustainable revenue streams through brand development, strategic partnerships and digital innovation.\n\nWhy Authentic\n\nYou’ll be able to access the resources and scale, while leveraging innovative technology and nimble environment. What we’re saying is, this isn’t your average day job. If you’re hungry to drive ideas into action and own your career, let’s chat. Our team is rapidly innovating to evolve and define the future of our brands. With the help of some of the brightest minds in retail, marketing, licensing, legal and more, we are building the intersection of digital and experiential marketing to help achieve that mission. We reimagine, evolve and transform brands! At Authentic, we foster an inclusive workplace where diversity of thought and expertise drive competitive advantage. Our global teams are built by go-getters who contribute unique perspectives and push the boundaries of creativity and innovation. Headquartered in New York City, Authentic has offices in major metropolitan cities including Los Angeles and Miami, as well as Toronto, Mexico City, London, and Shanghai.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nThe Graphic Designer will join our Creative team, reporting to the VP, Creative. You'll partner on the creation of compelling brand storytelling and creative development for Authentic Partnerships and Collaborations, Authentic Studios and Authentic Entertainment. You'll be responsible for graphic design in apparel design and mock ups, new business and category pitches, to handling all of the day-to-day creative needs.\n\nWhat You’ll Be Working On\n\nConceptualize and create tailored, brand-right pitches and presentations including mockups, infographics, showcasing strong layout and typography abilities\nTranslate and adapt existing brand guidelines to support overall business needs with creative for product development, brand extensions, POP, signage, and more\nDevelop logos, branding, and packaging as well as associated guidelines\nAssist in the creation of brand books, style guides, brand guides, etc.\nEvent graphics & collateral\nDevelop a deep understanding of the brands and how to convey their voices and personality across mediums\nEnsure consistency of communications across all creative touchpoints and adherence to brand standards throughout the creative process\n\nMust Haves\n\n3-5 years of experience as a Graphic Designer\nAdobe Creative Suite with focus on InDesign, Photoshop, Illustrator; Web/Video and/or retouching experience a plus\nExperienced in creative problem solving, innovative visual storytelling, and working strategically across disciplines\nComfortability in fast pace, nimble environment\nMust be able to set priorities and multi-task\nMust have portfolio to submit for review\n\nPrimary Location Salary Range:\n\n$80,000 - $90,000\n\nAuthentic is an equal-opportunity employer and we value and embrace the diversity and inclusion of all Team Members. We do not discriminate on the basis of gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, race, national origin, disability, age, marital status, protected veteran status, or other legally protected status.\n\nFor individuals with disabilities or religious obligations who would like to request an accommodation, please contact talent@authentic.com\n\nTo access Authentic' s Privacy Policy, which contains information regarding data collected from job applicants and how we use it, please click here:\n\nhttps://www.authentic.com/privacy-policy", 'Who We Need\nWe’re here because we want someone awesome to join our crew: A Graphic Designer who can execute creative across a variety of platforms. The ideal candidate should be comfortable managing multiple design projects independently, with the guidance and support from others who are part of the larger creative and production team. It’s imperative that this designer is a strong communicator and collaborator and is confident with their work being viewed by potentially millions of people.\n\nWho We Are\nWe are a creative agency called HangarFour within a big PR firm called DKC. But who we actually are is a scrappy, close-knit crew of multi-talented creatives who play a variety of roles. With us, the ability to step in and step up to make ideas happen is what makes us stand out to our clients and the industry. It is essential that you have that vision too.\n\nResponsibilities:\nExecute design projects for multiple clients across multiple platforms. Projects may include ad materials, event signage, social media posts, package design and digital collateral (invitations, e-blasts, web banners, gif files and more)\nDesign and produce eye-catching and professional proposal decks using InDesign and PowerPoint\nSource compelling and appropriate images\nParticipate in developing and maintaining brands’ identity, strategy, and positioning\nEnsure that designs meet both agency and client expectations, are within budget, and are delivered on time\nCommunicate project status, timeline and delivery of information to both clients as well as internal teams in a prompt and clear manner\nBe an active participant in brainstorming sessions, planning, design and department meetings\nMaintain well-organized and accessible paperwork, renderings, and digital design files\nStay current in design trends, new software and technologies, production techniques, props/design elements, and vendor products\n\nDesired Skills & Experience:\n4+ years in relevant graphic design role\nMastery of the Adobe Creative Suite (Illustrator, InDesign and Photoshop are musts), Microsoft Office (especially PowerPoint), Photoshop\nAbility to prioritize multiple projects and meet deadlines\nProfessional demeanor and ability to interact with senior client-side executives\nKeen awareness of design trends\nWork varied shifts, including occasional weekends and holidays\n\nAttitude Basics:\nSelf-starter and ability to self-manage: you will be working closely with the Creative team, but we will rely on you to keep your own deadlines on our fast-paced calendar of projects and make sure that all your images are pixel perfect!\nA player we can count on: Always organized so you can move fast with us and willing to put in the extra time and effort with the team on projects when needed\nSomeone who makes others’ lives easier: When something goes wrong, you can figure out a way to solve it with the team and get the job done\nFervid desire to learn and ability to receive feedback while maintaining a great attitude so we can ALL improve.', 'Mercer Advisors is a different kind of wealth management firm. We exist so that our clients don’t have to worry about money. Our firm was founded in 1985, on the belief that families at all wealth levels would benefit from a fully unified approach to managing their money – “A family office for your family.” We connect the dots of our clients’ financial lives by unifying planning, investing, taxes, estate, insurance, trust, and more. Today, we proudly serve over 25,000 families, across over 90 cities, with over $45 Billion in assets entrusted to our care. And we do this as an independent, national fiduciary – which means we are committed to always working in the clients’ best interest.\n\nWhen you join our team, you will find that it is different from what you typically see in our industry. Our client-facing professionals of in-house experts are 50% women, as is our overall employee base. We bring together the best talent wherever they live –with no formal headquarters, and many flexible working arrangements – so we can assemble the best team.\n\nSummary\n\nThe Jr. Graphic Designer is a key contributor to the marketing team and will work closely with the Art Director and other Graphic Designers. This role will help to ensure marketing materials are updated in a timely fashion and proper brand guidelines are followed. In addition, the Jr. Graphic Designer is responsible for assisting the Graphic Designer and Art Director with managing the visual and creative marketing assets across digital and print channels. This includes collateral, social media assets, email templates, direct mail and advertising for corporate marketing as well as for local marketing initiatives.\n\nIn addition to the above-mentioned responsibilities, this role assists with:\n\nUpdating and/or modifying existing marketing and sales materials ensuring adherence to all applicable brand guidelines\nWorking with other members of the creative team in design and development of templates, marketing materials, and more\nCreating and updating sales and client presentations as appropriate\nResponsible for updating employee titles and bios in all locations where the bios reside, e.g., collateral, presentation slides\nManaging and editing various photo assets including employee headshots\nDesigning, creating, updating, and maintaining excellent presentations, charts, and infographics to support the communications teams\nIncorporate the company’s brand guidelines, aesthetics, and tone into designs.\nAssist in the maintenance of brand guidelines\n\nRequirements:\n\nBachelor’s degree in graphic design or similar field\n2-4 years of experience in graphic design with a portfolio of work\nProficiency with Microsoft Office and Adobe Creative Suite including PowerPoint, Word, InDesign, and Photoshop\nWilling to learn new technologies\n\nKnowledge, Skills and Abilities:\n\nKnowledge of basic marketing design skills and what will drive response\nExcellent time management, problem-solving skills, and ability to adhere to a project timelines\nTeam player who can work collaboratively with other departments, partners, and marketing teammates\nMust be self-motivated, self-starter, and have a sense of urgency\nAbility to maintain a professional demeanor at all times and under all circumstances\nMust be able to manage multiple projects and prioritize deliverables\nExperience working in a fast paced, highly regulated, ever-changing industry\nSuperior attention to detail, with excellent verbal and written communication and proofreading skills\nStrong proven PowerPoint skills recommended\n\nWork Schedule\n\nMonday through Friday, 8:00AM – 5:00PM\n\nWorking Conditions\n\nProfessional office environment, daytime hours, working inside, standing, and sitting, will be assigned to a work station.\n\nBenefits:\n\nMercer Advisors offers a competitive and robust benefit package to our employees. Our benefit programs are focused on meeting all of our employees and their eligible dependents health and welfare needs. We offer the following:\n\nCompany Paid Basic Life & AD&D Insurance\nCompany Paid Short-Term and Long-Term Disability Insurance\nSupplemental Life & AD&D; Short-Term Disability; Accident; Critical Illness; and Hospital Indemnity Insurance\nThree medical plans offerings including two High Deductible Health Plans and a Traditional Co-Pay medical plan\nHealth Savings Account (HSA) with company contributions on a per pay period basis if enrolled in either HDHP medical plan\nTwo comprehensive Dental Plans\nVision Insurance Plan\nDependent Care Savings Account for child and dependent care\n14 Company Paid Holidays with a full week off at Thanksgiving\nGenerous paid time off program for vacation and sick days\nEmployee Assistance Plan\nFamily Medical Leave\nPaid Parental Leave (6 weeks)\nMaternity benefits utilizing company paid STD, any supplemental STD, plus Parental Leave (6 weeks) to provide time for recovery, baby bonding, and enjoying your family time\nAdoption Assistance Reimbursement Program\nCompany Paid Concierge Services for you and your loved ones for the spectrum of caring needs for your aging parents, young children, life’s challenges and more\n401(k) Retirement Plan with both Traditional and Roth plans with per pay period match\nPet Insurance\n\nWe are not accepting unsolicited resumes from agencies and/or search firms for this job posting.\n\nMercer Advisors provides equal employment opportunity to all applicants and employees without regard to age, color, disability, gender, marital status, national origin, race, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity and expression, physical or mental disability, genetic predisposition or carrier status, or any other characteristic protected by law in accordance with all applicable federal, state, and local laws. Mercer Advisors provides equal employment opportunity in all aspects of employment and employee relations, including recruitment, hiring, training and development, promotion, transfer, demotion, termination, layoff, compensation, benefits, and all other terms, conditions, and privileges of employment in accordance with applicable federal, state, and local laws.', 'Bonfire Effect Designer\ngraphic design firestarter with meticulous follow through.\nDo you consider yourself one of the unique designers who can build a PPT to look amazing AND function seamlessly? Would people describe you as detail-oriented, self-starter, who can produce high-quality designs that provide efficient solutions? If this sounds like you, then pull up a chair, and let’s chat around the Bonfire.\n\nthe role.\nAt Bonfire Effect, the Graphic Designer is a core position on our creative team responsible for delivering high-quality, original designs. As a technical expert, you know how to get the job done accurately to simplify complex information with stunning visuals. You will be challenged to think creatively to elevate a brand while designing within their brand guidelines. Never a dull moment, you will be working on multiple projects for a variety of B2B clients.\n\nwho you are:\nFearlessly creative. Produces professionally designed, content-driven, visually engaging layouts and presentations for marketing and event materials.\nSees the details and builds designs on a grid. With a strong eye for detail, this individual ensures all design work is accurately built and delivered on time and within the budget.\nDoes what\'s right. By designing with honesty and integrity you create smart, ownable designs that elevate our clients\' brand.\nAn expert. Willing to share feedback and insights to your team from your design perspective to help solve problems.\nEffective communicator. Knows the power of clear communication to guide a team, manage your time, and stay organized.\nValue-driven. Lives out the Bonfire Core Values (Be fearlessly creative, Do what’s right, Let go and have fun, Spread contagious love)\n\nwhat you’ll need.\nMinimum Requirements:\nExperience in Adobe InDesign, Illustrator, Photoshop and Microsoft Powerpoint\nMinimum of 3 years of agency or related design experience\nBachelor\'s degree or equivalent in fine art, graphic design, or similar discipline\nExperience designing visually appealing professional layouts utilizing typography, graphics, and imagery for multiple clients in print and digital format.\nA knack for creating designs that elevate the client’s brand while adhering to a client brand guide\nAble to self-manage and self-organize while coordinating with assigned teams on multiple projects\nDemonstrates strong problem solving skills\nDesire to grow professionally\n\nthe bonfire effect.\nA thriving creative branding and marketing agency, Bonfire Effect boasts a passionate team of problem solvers who put in the work to ignite our clients’ brands – whether that’s a local nonprofit or large global technology company. We’re a diverse crew of folks who start fires. Not literally (though we do have an annual Bonfire bonfire), but the ones that spark change and illuminate new opportunities. We work smart, play hard, and live with passion. Some of us love websites, some love email campaigns, some love PowerPoint (J/K, no one loves PPT but if you are a PPT whiz, you might be looking at the right role). Some of us love videos of raccoons eating with their little hands. We don’t judge. We embrace our differences and look for ways to fuel each other’s interests.\n\nthe benefits:\n22 total accrued vacation, sick/wellness days and 8 holidays to help you rest & recharge with loved ones\nSalary range between $55k to $65k + bonus opportunities\n100% medical + vision and dental coverage\n401(k) retirement savings plan with employer match\nShort-term + long-term disability\nLife Insurance and Accidental Death and Dismemberment coverage\nAnnual investment in learning & development\nBeer & nitro coffee on tap (but ya gotta be willing to "Beer Sherpa" occasionally)\n\nhow to apply.\nIf you are interested in applying to the Graphic Designer position, please complete each of the steps below:\n1. Click the link and complete the 2-question survey:\nhttps://go.cultureindex.com/p/NfwkS1UzAqxjjWD\n2. Send your resume and portfolio to careers@bonfireeffect.com.\nOnce you have completed these 2 steps we will reach out for next steps in the process.\n\nsimply put.\nSkilled professional graphic designer\nStrong attention to detail\nAbility to problem solve and complete work independently\nExperience working with brand guides, project deadlines, and client budgets\n\nthe finer print: Here are a few other shenanigans to look forward to as part of the Bonfire crew:\nHaving deep intellectual conversations around Excel formulas\nStarting a fire with a single match\nLiking (or learning to like) bikes – of either the fossil fuel or pedaling variety\nNot being afraid to light something on fire (safely and legally)\nPlaying at least one game of pinball blindfolded\nBeing able to work under fire (not literal fire… the NERF dart kind)\nDeveloping a rich appreciation for obscure movie references, strange sound effects, and good bourbon', 'Department\n\nMarketing\n\nWe are Walker & Dunlop. We are one of the largest providers of capital to the commercial real estate industry, enabling real estate owners and operators to bring their visions of communities — where people live, work, shop, and play — to life. We are committed to creating meaningful social, environmental, and economic change in our communities. We believe seeking diverse talent and promoting the inclusion of all perspectives are more than moral imperatives – they are critical to our success and ability to innovate and grow.\n\nWe are looking for an innovative Graphic Designer to join Walker & Dunlop, one of FORTUNE Magazine’s 20 fastest growing public companies and a Great Place to Work®. This role will report to the Creative Director. As a graphic designer, you will be an active and important participant in the design process, from concept to creation, to support the needs of the Marketing team. We are looking for designers who are highly creative, passionate, and motivated to produce – qualities essential to help drive our marketing to the next level. If you are a self-starter, this is a rare opportunity to join a growing in-house agency in a successful company intent on building an industry-leading marketing program.\n\nWhat You Will Be Doing\n\nActively participate in group brainstorming/concept development sessions with the Creative Director and/or brokers\nInterpret needs and create innovative designs to effectively convey desired ideas\nTake ownership of all areas of the design process from initial prototype to creation to the preparation of final mechanicals\nCreate eye-catching offering memorandums, brochures, presentations, and other marketing collateral that preserves and elevates the brand\nWork closely with the Creative Director and brokers, taking direction and implementing changes to improve design and consistently adhere to brand standards\nManage and document the approval process needed for each type of project\nCollaborate across the creative team and help with other projects, as needed\nPrioritize projects and handle multiple tasks efficiently\nProvide input to continually improve the creative process\nAssist in the QA process\nMaintain a positive attitude and share a passion for growing the Walker & Dunlop brand with other career-minded individuals across the company\nCommunicate and problem-solve daily with teammates, clients, vendors, and other stakeholders, often in combination with travel\nLearn and expand creative skills to build a career in graphic design\n\nThe Education And Experience We’re Looking For\n\nBachelor’s degree in Graphic Design or related discipline\n2 plus years of experience as a Graphic Designer\nB2B design experience preferred\n\nWhat Skills You Should Have\n\nHigh level of proficiency with industry standard Adobe CC applications (Photoshop, Illustrator, and InDesign) and Microsoft Office Suite\nExperience creating multimedia presentations\nThorough understanding of marketing strategy and ability to execute strategy with design solutions\nExperience working with clients to identify needs and present solutions\nStrong data visualization design skills\nExceptional typography skills\nAbility to take direction, work quickly and efficiently to meet deadlines, and communicate clearly and effectively with collaborators across all levels of the organization\nMeticulous attention to detail and accuracy\nSelf-motivated, with the ability to multi-task, work independently and learn technical information quickly\nFlexible problem-solver able to adapt to changing circumstances and needs\nStrong project management skills, organizational skills, and time management skills\nExcellent teamwork to engage productively with other design professionals\nThe ability and desire to keep up to date with commercial design trends to stay on the leading edge of creativity\nAbility to show ownership of your work, take on challenges and acknowledge growth opportunities, and demonstrate patience when learning new processes\nCourtesy, respect, and thoughtfulness in teaming with colleagues and other stakeholders\n\nStill reading? Then we think you should apply!\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nThe opportunity to join one of Fortune Magazine’s Great Places to Work winners from 2015-2023\nComprehensive benefit options* that have earned Walker & Dunlop the silver level of the 2022 Cigna Healthy Workforce Designation™, some of which include:\nUp to 83% subsidized medical payroll deductions\nCompetitive dental and vision benefits\n401(k) + match\nPre-tax transit and commuting benefits\nA robust health and wellness program – earn cash rewards and gain access to resources that\n\npromote health, engagement, and balance\n\nPaid maternity and parental leave, as well as other family paid leave programs\nCompany-paid life, short and long-term disability insurance\nHealth Savings Account and Healthcare and Dependent Care Flexible Spending\nCommitment to diversity, equity, and inclusion, with employee resource groups organizing activities and providing a space for open communication\nCareer development opportunities\nEmpowerment and encouragement to give back – volunteer hours and donation matching\nEligibility may vary based on average number of hours worked\n\nEEO Statement\n\nWe are committed to equity in all steps of the recruitment and employment experience. We believe in equal access to opportunities in our workplace. We do not tolerate discrimination, including harassment, based on any characteristic protected by applicable law, such as race, color, national origin, religion, gender identity, sexual orientation, sex, age, disability, veteran or military status, and genetic information. We strive to be a safe place to ask questions, build professional relationships, and develop careers.\n\nSPAM\n\nPlease be wary of recruitment scams. An indication of a scam might be a request for sensitive or bank information at the time of application or emails coming from a non walkerdunlop.com email address. Please call us at 301.215.5500, if you have any concerns about information requested during or after the application process.', "Location: Falls Church, Virginia\n\nJob Type: Contract to Perm\n\nCompensation Range $30 - 48 per hour\n\nCella has partnered with a well-known professional services company in search of a Graphic Designer to join their team. In this role, you will be supporting the brand's in-house agency. The ideal candidate will have to be comfortable working within brand guidelines and 3+ years of experience creating unique and innovative designs across multiple channels.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nProactively understand and gain knowledge of our brands, target audiences and competitor activities.\nDevelop creative ideas and concepts, often in partnership with the Creative Director and other Senior Designers and Copywriters.\nProcess and produce multiple projects in a short time frame\nWorking with stock imagery/music/etc to create pixel perfect designs and come up with unique visuals.\nManage multiple projects simultaneously under the pressure of deadlines.\nApply style guides creatively while upholding brand identity.\nCapture content as needed.\nUnderstand business objectives and find creative solutions to help achieve objectives.\n\n\nQualifications:\n\nExperience level: Experienced\nEducation: Bachelors\nPortfolio showing a range of experience, concepts, and visual styles.\nMinimum of 3-5 years relative Design experience, preferably in a design firm, advertising or in-house creative department.\nExperience working with a marketing department.\nKnowledge of design fundamentals, & messaging hierarchy.\nExperience working on direct response materials and designing for a range of marketing channels including email, banner ads, social, landing pages, print collateral.\nExcellent working knowledge of Adobe Suite.\nCommunication skills with the ability to work in a team environment.\nBrings creative, organizational problem solving.\nExperience developing rich media and other forms of online advertising.\n\n\nJOBID: 1003343\n\nEqual Opportunity Employer: Race, Color, Religion, Sex, Sexual Orientation, Gender Identity, National Origin, Age, Genetic Information, Disability, Protected Veteran Status, or any other legally protected group status.\n\nAt Cella, a randstad digital company, we welcome people of all abilities and want to ensure that our hiring and interview process meets the needs of all applicants. If you require a reasonable accommodation to make your application or interview experience a great one, please contact HRsupport@randstadusa.com.\n\nPay offered to a successful candidate will be based on several factors including the candidate's education, work experience, work location, specific job duties, certifications, etc. In addition, Cella by randstad digital offers a comprehensive benefits package, including health, an incentive and recognition program, and 401K contribution (all benefits are based on eligibility).\n\nApplications accepted on ongoing basis until filled.", 'GRAPHIC DESIGNER\nReports To: CCO, Lead Designer\nSalary: $60-75k\nCompany: Brand Design Agency\nLocation: Los Angeles (must be willing to work in person)\nCommitment: Part-time\nStarting date: Immediate\n\nCompany Overview\nA brand design agency specializing in branding and digital for brands and icons in the fashion and luxury industries that move culture forward.\n\nDescription\nThe company is seeking a talented Graphic Designer with a strong focus on visual identity design, packaging, and branding. The ideal candidate has and knowledge or interest of the luxury and fashion industries.\n\nResponsibilities\nWork alongside the design team to create innovative visual identities for brands\nConceptualize and design responsive digital experiences\nEnsure brand consistency while offering a fresh approach to design\nFollow creative work from concept to production\nManage project load while coordinating with project teams and management on schedules, requirements, goals and assignments as needed\n\nQualifications\n2-3 years of work experience as a Graphic Designer, Digital Designer or related field\nElevated eye for design, layout, typography and ability to adhere to brand guidelines\nExcellent communication, time management and organizational skills, deadline-driven\nHighly creative & innovative\nExperience in the Agency and/or Luxury industry is preferred', "HOK designs buildings and spaces that respond to the needs of people and the environment. Our designers are rooted in technical excellence, driven by imagination and focused on a solitary goal: to deliver solutions that inspire clients and communities.\n\nWe are currently seeking a Graphic Designer to join our Firmwide Communications team. As a Graphic Designer, you will be responsible for creating graphic images for use on various media platforms and marketing through out the firm. Responsibilities and duties include, but not limited to,\n\nDesign graphic content for the website, graphics for social media, data visualizations, infographics and other content for diverse platforms.\nAssist Visual Storyteller in creating assets for video and motion graphics.\nFormat graphic assets for the website and manage the media library in the CMS.\nCollaborate with Firmwide Communications team and other departments on project requirements.\nShow flexibility for occasional contributions to special projects beyond regular responsibilities.\n\nRequired Skills\n\nProficiency in Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign).\nProficiency in MS Office such as Outlook, PowerPoint and Word.\nExperience collaborating on video and motion graphics assets is a plus.\nStrong illustration skills are a plus.\nWorking knowledge of Premier Pro and/or After Effects is a plus.\nProblem-solving ability, excellent service orientation, and effective project management.\nAbility to work independently and as part of a team.\nGood interpersonal and communication skills.\nKnowledge about design elements, such as color and composition.\nMust possess design talent, creative energy and organizational skills.\nAbility to anticipate, identify and troubleshoot problems and recognize alternative actions.\nAbility to provide excellent, consistent service to internal and external clients in a supportive and professional manner.\nAbility to effectively meet deadlines.\nAbility to work independently and as part of a team environment and must possess good interpersonal skills.\n\nQualifications\n\nPortfolio Requirements\n\nApplicants are required to submit a portfolio showcasing their proficiency in graphic design. The portfolio should demonstrate the following:\n\nA solid foundation in design principles, including but not limited to color theory, composition, and typography.\nExamples that highlight versatility across various types of projects, such as social media graphics, data visualizations, website content, and other relevant mediums.\nProvide insights into the candidate's creativity, problem-solving skills and the ability to translate concepts into visually compelling designs.\n\nEducation And Experience\n\nBachelor's degree in Graphic Design or comparable equivalent required.\n3 plus years of related experience in with the design, development and implementation of graphic design projects required.\n\nHOK is committed to providing our employees with a comprehensive benefits plan to meet their current and future needs. Benefits include medical, dental and vision coverage, 401(K) savings plans; disability, life and accident insurance; paid time off (PTO); and parental leave. In addition, HOK employees enjoy a flexible work schedule with their option to work remotely on Mondays and Fridays.\n\nHOK is a drug-free workplace. HOK is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, religion, color, national origin, sex, age, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender identity, status as a protected veteran or status as a qualified individual with a disability, or any other characteristic protected by applicable Federal, State or Local law.\n\nCompensation is based on experience, qualifications, education and location. The typical salary range for this position in New York is $61,000 - $68,000.\n\nAdditional Locations\n\n1065 Ave of the Americas, 6th Flr, New York, New York\nCanal House, 3223 Grace St NW, Washington, District of Columbia\n1 Logan Square, Suite 1510, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania\n\nLocation\n\n133 Peachtree Street NE, Suite 4800, Atlanta, Georgia\n\nPosition Type\n\nFull-Time/Regular", "How you fill your 52 weeks is your business. Helping you find your next opportunity is ours.\nWe are searching for a Graphic Designer to join the Design & Experience team for our financial industry client. This role offers an opportunity to develop high-quality assets that convey an engaging story and support a cohesive brand vision across various platforms. As a graphic designer, you’ll be part of a dynamic, collegial, and inclusive working environment.\n\nWho we’re looking for/About you:\nA bachelor’s degree in graphic design or an equivalent field is required, as are five years of professional experience in visual design or a related field.\nPortfolio demonstrating a range of design techniques and skills, a solid background in typography, and an appreciation for a clean and impactful aesthetic.\nAbility to take initiative, be curious, and excellent communication and interpersonal skills.\nKnack for project management, demonstrated technical prowess, impressive design sensibilities, and a rigorous and proactive work ethic.\nHighly organized individuals with keen attention to detail and the ability to advance multiple projects with varying deadlines simultaneously.\nFluent in both Mac and PC environments, proficient in Adobe Creative (InDesign, Illustrator, Photoshop, etc.) and Microsoft Office Suites.\nExperience with UX/UI and data visualization skills are a plus.\n\nWhat you'll do day-to-day:\n\nIn this role, you’ll work on a wide range of projects and media, conceptualizing, strategizing, and producing highly creative digital and print deliverables. Responsibilities include supporting firmwide branding, marketing, and recruiting efforts through sales and recruitment material, core brand assets, document templates, presentations and data visuals, and website graphics. You’ll also be responsible for managing and helping organize digital assets. This role will provide the opportunity to collaborate with groups across the firm, develop creative solutions, and contribute to enhancing the firm’s brand.\n\nLogistics:\nExpected annual base salary: $100,000 to $115,000\nLocation: Hybrid, New York City\n\nWhy Work with 52 Limited:\nWe are committed to fostering a people-first candidate experience that benefits our talent, clients, and community. 52 Limited encourages a diversity of applicants of all backgrounds and identities to apply. Let us know if you need reasonable accommodation during the application or interview process."]


